%S A396490 6,36,1962,3084,83118,311916,4041726,94910688,123375750,2065680720,
%T A396490 2250090570,4816025460
%N A396490 Area of the smallest convex polygon (by area) which can be triangulated into n different primitive Pythagorean triangles.
%H A396490 Charles L. Hohn, <a href="/A396490/a396490.pdf">Example illustration of a(9)</a>
%e A396490 a(1) = 6: a 3,4,5 triangle.
%e A396490 a(2) = 36: a 3,4,5 and a 5,12,13 triangle adjoined at their sides of length 5, in any orientation.
%e A396490 a(3) = 1962: 5,12,13, 13,84,85, and 36,77,85, oriented such that the sides of length 5 and 36 are not adjacent.
%o A396490 (PARI) \\ see Hohn link in A396266, using require_convex_polygon = 1.
%Y A396490 Cf. A396266 (smallest simple polygon), A024406 (areas of primitive Pythagorean triangles).
%K A396490 nonn,more,new
%O A396490 1,1
